Sokoto State Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal has been conferred with the UNESCO 2018 Education Solution Stakeholders Award. The award was presented to Tambuwal at the United Nations headquarters in New York. Chairman of the award committee, Dr Hul Hsu, said the governor was nominated for the award in recognition of his contribution to quality education in his state. A statement signed by the Senior Special Assistant to the Governor on Media and Public Affairs, Abdullahi S. Danko, said that Tambuwal was represented by the state commissioner for higher education, Dr Mohammad Jabbi Kilgori and the chairman house committee on education Rep Aminu Bala Bodinga. Tambuwal had in 2015 declared state of emergency in education in the state.